The Securities and Exchange Commissionsaid it will hold a public hearing against Martin Saposnick,who was a co-underwriter of a 1983 public offering of NorthAtlantic Airlines Inc.    The SEC claims that Saposnick, chairman of MarsanSecurities Co Inc, knew the offering prspectus failed toadequately disclose the company's delinquent federal and statetaxes and its inability to pay debts when due.    No specific date was set. The SEC said the hearing willdetermine whether Saposnick misrepresented compliance withNASDAQ and if so, will determine remedial action. Reuter&#3;